  "prompt": "Was Charles Lee related to Robert E. Lee?",
  "response": "Charles Lee and Robert E. Lee were not closely related, but they were part of the broader Lee family of Virginia, a prominent family in American history. Charles Lee (1758\u20131815) served as the United States Attorney General from 1795 to 1801 under Presidents George Washington and John Adams. Robert E. Lee (1807\u20131870), on the other hand, was the Confederate general during the American Civil War.\n\nBoth men were connected through the larger Lee family lineage, but they were not directly related in terms of close familial ties like siblings or first cousins. Their connection was more distant and related to the broader family tree of the Lee family of Virginia.",
